ions of the past through a multiplication of perspectives and voices.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aJamaica Kincaid. 4aPostcolonial Studies. 4aUSA. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z97831113182640 cEPUBz97831110275240 cprintz978311101861440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111027500zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111027500zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111027500/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131826-4 EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6 EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA